AB  - Bangladesh is a major coastal nation and the negative effects of salinity intrusion there are severe. The food security of the salt-affected region is seriously threatened by the impact of salinity intrusion on agriculture. The study was conducted to assess the changes in Land Use and Land Cover due to increasing salinity and to identify the impacts of salinity intrusion on agriculture. Technical and scientific knowledge helped to build this paper along with primary and secondary data by using different tools and instruments. The results revealed how land use features have changed over the past 22 years between 2000 and 2022 in Gabura Union, Shyamnagar, Satkhira, Bangladesh. The NDSI map shows the coverage of salinity-affected areas has increased at a higher level. Especially the cropland area has reduced quantitatively from what it was in 2000 and a great fall in cropland happened in 2009. The agricultural production of different crops and vegetables has also decreased at a high rate during this period. Salinity has challenging impacts on agriculture. Some suggestions and guidelines are also included in this paper which will help the local farmers of the coastal area of Bangladesh to mitigate and adapt to the impact of salinity intrusion on Agriculture.
